comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T17:05:17.230Z",maintainer-agent,"Audit 2026-06-07 (PR pass): docs/CI findings — SHIPPED pm-7tvx (MCP tool-count drift + live-count smoke), pm-t73k (CONTRIBUTING PR-matrix), pm-ji5c (CodeQL SHA pin + contract test). See ADR pm-96wm."
  "2026-06-25T00:41:53.152Z",codex-audit-20260625,"Audit evidence: GitHub main CI/Docs/CodeQL baseline was green before changes. Repository settings remediated via gh API: secret-scanning push protection enabled, main branch protection added with required CI/Docs/CodeQL checks, strict up-to-date checks, linear history, no force pushes/deletions, and required conversation resolution. Changelog check passed unchanged via pm-changelog 2026.6.20; contracts snapshot current."
  "2026-06-25T00:51:11.872Z",codex-audit-20260625,"CI follow-up: PR static gate correctly failed because changelog was regenerated before closing pm-js02/pm-zqes/pm-mthy/pm-r642. Regenerated CHANGELOG.md with pnpm changelog:pm after closing those items; managed-extension timestamp-only churn excluded."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T10:08:27.982Z",audit-docs-tests-agent,"Audit findings summary (2026-06-07):\n\nDOCS DRIFT:\n- ARCHITECTURE.md storage layout missing plans/, stories/, schema/, checkpoints/, runtime/ (pm-mcgf)\n- pm-linked-test-adapters package undocumented in EXTENSIONS.md + TESTING.md (pm-yj8n)\n- SDK.md registerImporter/registerExporter missing 3rd options arg example (pm-btwe)\n- ARCHITECTURE.md: no performance/startup-latency section (pm-p37b)\n- ARCHITECTURE.md: no new-command wiring checklist (pm-zyse)\n- TESTING.md: no coverage governance section (pm-othr)\n- TESTING.md: no search eval golden-query harness docs (pm-eg9k)\n- RELEASING.md: no silent-skip debugging, pm-changelog separate-repo context, or tag-force-fetch docs (pm-97yv)\n\nCI / RELEASE:\n- codeql.yml uses @v3 floating tags, not SHA-pinned (pm-ji5c)\n- nightly.yml has no failure alerting (pm-ehbb)\n- 120-file unit cap: tests/unit/ has 122 files; governance test missing (pm-wc0d)\n\nTESTS / COVERAGE:\n- MCP pm_context, pm_contracts, pm_plan, pm_health: no integration tests (pm-8d00)\n- close-many --rollback restore: no integration test for end-to-end cycle (pm-7p4w)\n- schema add-type/remove-type round-trip: no integration test with governance (pm-4dtf)\n- background-refresh (instant mutations): no integration test for non-blocking guarantee (pm-5rge)\n- Windows path-separator: no explicit cross-platform coverage in fs-utils/store-paths (pm-tq5t)\n\nALL GREEN / WELL-COVERED:\n- COMMANDS.md: gc --scope locks, history --diff, stats --storage all documented\n- COMMANDS.md: schema add/remove-type/status fully documented\n- COMMANDS.md: close-many, update-many with rollback documented\n- AGENT_GUIDE.md: remediation_map and --fix-hints documented\n- RELEASING.md: one-time setup, automated daily driver, workflow steps all current\n- release.yml + auto-release.yml: all actions SHA-pinned; SENTRY_PERSONAL_ADMIN_TOKEN guard present\n- remediation-registry: has dedicated integration test (remediation-registry.spec.ts)\n- Schema customization: unit test coverage present (schema-command, settings-validator, item-type-definition)\n- docs.yml: quality:docs-skills + quality:docs-links gates both present\n\nADR CANDIDATES (not creating items per hard rules):\n1. 'Nightly CI: informational vs required' - should Windows/Node-next nightly failures block release?\n2. 'CodeQL action pinning exemption' - should codeql-action be SHA-pinned or exempt due to frequent SHA changes?\n3. 'Search eval gate: advisory vs blocking' - should nDCG eval gate be promoted to blocking in CI?\n4. 'Coverage governance: include+exclude pattern' - the dual-list strategy is an architectural decision not yet written as ADR"
